11/04/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The renovated St. 
Paul the Apostle International Airport in Ohrid opened on Sunday (April 10th) with Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski and other guests in attendance. 
The Turkish concessionaire, TAV Airports Holding, invested 10m euros in the reconstruction. 
"This project is significant for Ohrid and the development of tourism in the region. 
We hope that the reconstruction will contribute to the airport's efficiency and naturally increase the number of passengers," Gruevski said at the ceremony. 
TAV CEO Savi Sener announced that the reconstruction of another airport, Skopje, is expected to open on September 8th, Macedonia's Independence Day. 
(MIA, Makfax, OhridNews - 10/04/11)
